commit.message: Fix docstring wording in ht-merge
Add ht-update-with!

Fix ht-reject! docstring mismatch with actual behavior

The actual behavior is that, when FUNCTION returns non-nil for an
entry, the entry is rejected.

Entries are kept when FUNCTION returns falsy for them (ht-reject's way
of describing it), or deleted when FUNCTION returns non-nil.

Fix symbol collision in ht-select-keys

Previously if the value happens to be the interned symbol
key-not-found, it would be treated as not present even though it is
present.

    (ht->alist
     (ht-select-keys
      (ht ("a" 'key-not-found)
          ("b" 'b)
          ("c" 'c))
      (list "a" "b" "c")))
    ;; -> (("c" . c) ("b" . b))
    ;; should be (("c" . c) ("b" . b) ("a" . key-not-found))

This fixes it.
Remove build badge as it's already visible in the GitHub UI
Run cask after checkout
Switch to GitHub Actions
Add changelog skeleton
Test ht-equal-p with more deeply nested ht

Make nested ht comparable

Before this commit nested hash table could never equal to itself because
a hash table does not pass `equal` test.

Fix emacs native compilation warning

```
 ■  Warning (comp): ht.el:186:2: Warning: docstring has wrong usage of
unescaped single quotes (use \= or different quoting)
 ■  Warning (comp): ht.el:210:2: Warning: docstring has wrong usage of
unescaped single quotes (use \= or different quoting)
 ■  Warning (comp): ht.el:229:2: Warning: docstring has wrong usage of
unescaped single quotes (use \= or different quoting)
 ■  Warning (comp): ht.el:247:2: Warning: docstring has wrong usage of
unescaped single quotes (use \= or different quoting)
```

To reproduce, have emacs built with native compilation and notice the
compilation logs. You can then open the offending file and run `M-x
emacs-lisp-native-compile-and-load` before and after the changes to see the
warning is removed.

Roll version

Closes #40

Update changelog for v2.3

See also #40.

Fix return behaviour of ht-get*.

Using prog1 would return the initial value of the table argument. The modified
value of the table must be returned manually instead.

Fixes #38

Use define-inline instead of defsubst.

Fixes #33
Declare functions as side-effect-free when possible.
